  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Nutritionists & Dietitians
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        People seeking nutrition coaching have usually tried other things. They're skeptical. The barrier to booking isn't price — it's belief that it will actually work for them. Client transformation testimonials break that skepticism faster than credentials, certifications, or methodology explanations.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">The "someone like me" effect in nutrition testimonials</h2>
      <p>When a prospect reads a testimonial from someone in their specific situation — same age, same struggle, same failed attempts — it creates a powerful "if it worked for them it could work for me" moment. SocialProof helps you collect and display these stories prominently on your booking page, turning skeptics into inquiries.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What nutrition client testimonials should communicate</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Real results:</strong> "Lost 28 lbs in 4 months without ever feeling deprived. The meal plans actually tasted good."</li>
        <li><strong>Sustainable change:</strong> "For the first time I'm not dieting — I'm just eating better. And it's been 18 months."</li>
        <li><strong>Non-judgmental approach:</strong> "She never made me feel bad about my history. Just focused on what comes next."</li>
        <li><strong>Medical complexity:</strong> "She worked around my PCOS and thyroid issues in ways no one had tried before."</li>
        <li><strong>Lifestyle fit:</strong> "I told her I hate cooking and travel for work. She built a plan around that. It actually works."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Compliance note for health professionals</h2>
      <p>Nutritionists and dietitians should ensure testimonials are truthful and representative. Avoid implying specific medical outcomes. SocialProof gives you full editorial control — approve every testimonial before it goes live, and you can request clarifications before publishing.</p>

